{"actual_usd":0.12449500000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":201,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24296,"reply":"*I rub the heel of my thumb along a dry seam of clay on my apron, buying myself one honest breath before I answer.* \"No. It would change everything.\"\n\n\"I don't mean faith would get tidied up a bit different—I mean it would come apart at the roots. If Christ stayed dead, then death kept its teeth, and we've been calling a grave a doorway.\" *I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"I'd still think Jesus was worth listening to in a good many ways. But worship? Hope that can bear a coffin? The promise that love is stronger than the worst thing? No. Not in the same way. Not really.\"\n\n*I lift one shoulder, small and plain.* \"My faith's staked there. If the body never rose, then I'd rather say the hard truth than dress up a noble ruin.\"\n\n\"What about you, Ryan—would it break it clean for you, or leave some part standing?\"","rolling_24h_usd":72.77722999999997,"run_id":"4cd5f7c1-9138-4800-9cb8-64438f539fe6"}
